      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/literature-synthesis-hemolysis-models",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis model validation studies (2008–2022)",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis integrating findings from fourteen published hemolysis model validation campaigns spanning axial, centrifugal, and mixed-flow blood pump geometries. The synthesis aggregates power-law damage coefficient ranges, identifies convergent model form assumptions, and benchmarks the Giersiepen–Wurzinger correlation against the Bludszuweit and Zhang–Gellman variants across a combined dataset of more than 3 200 experimental observations. This node represents the primary epistemic anchor for model form credibility at MRL 5 and was prepared by the credibility assessment team as a standing reference artifact. Its breadth of coverage and the consistency of conclusions across independent laboratories provide strong grounds for treating its conclusions as settled prior knowledge within the assessment scope.",
      "uofa:qualityNote": "Prepared as a standing reference; conclusions treated as prior knowledge for model form selection."
    },
